    "narrative": "For this May 3rd slate, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on speed and favorable matchups to navigate a high-volume day. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98) is our standout play; while his #8 spot in the order is a slight drag, he faces a soft matchup against Meibrys Viloria\u2019s battery mate, and the combination of an 87% stolen base threat profile against the opposing starter and a significant \"Wind Out\" boost makes him the engine of our outfield. **Junior Caminero** (73.06) also earns high marks, benefiting from a robust 15% SP skill boost against Mahle, while **Trea Turner** (69.28) remains a foundational play, leveraging the #1 spot in the order and a favorable 4.41 xERA matchup against Paddack to solidify our stolen base potential.\n\nWe are carefully managing our platoon efficiency, particularly with **Colt Keith** (65.83) and **Gary Sanchez** (62.74), who both benefit from ideal order placement and favorable park factors. The most difficult bench decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion** (42.40), who carried respectable platoon splits against Matz but ultimately lacked the categorical urgency provided by the speed-heavy profiles of our starting outfielders. While **Kazuma Okamoto** (46.93) and **Dillon Dingler** (46.93) sit at the lower end of our active spectrum, their presence is mandated by the need to balance positional scarcity against the day's projections.\n\nRisk remains localized in our \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Dillon Dingler** and **Colt Keith**. Should their actual batting order drop significantly, their daily efficiency scores will require immediate re-calibration. Additionally, while **Yordan Alvarez** (60.46) carries an elite xwOBA, his score is tempered by a negative platoon split against the southpaw Suarez and a lower SP skill boost, making him a high-floor start rather than the explosive ceiling play we expect from **Pete Crow-Armstrong**. We continue to monitor **Christian Yelich** and **Zac Veen**, who remain sidelined, as we maximize our remaining games played for the week.",
